s="hfeed"><div class="post-22826 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-recipes-food"><h1 class="entry-title">Au Gratin Potato and Bacon Pizza Recipe and a Giveaway</h1><div class="post-info"><span class="date published time" title="2011-11-26T06:45:13-0500">November 26, 2011</span> By <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="http://blommi.com/author/Robin/" title="Posts by Robin" rel="author">Robin</a></span></span> <span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blommi.com/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza-recipe-and-a-giveaway/#comments">131 Comments</a></span></div><div class="entry-content"><p><a href="http://blommi.com/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza-recipe-and-a-giveaway/au-gratin-potato-pizza/" rel="attachment wp-att-22828"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-22828" title="au gratin potato pizza" src="http://blommi.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/au-gratin-potato-pizza.jpg" alt="au gratin potato pizza" width="590" height="409" /></a></p><p>As Americans we think of pizza first and foremost as tomato sauce and cheese covered crust, but in other parts of the world potatoes are seen as a common topping for this sort of food.Â  The French are particularly known for topping pizza like crusts with potato and onions.Â  The version of Potato Pizza, I am sharing here, is certainly not a lofty gourmet dish, but more something fun and easy.Â  It will throw off your kids, but they are bound to like it.</p><p>While I was making this my daughter looked on.Â  I could see some confusion on her face, as I topped the dough with the cheesy potatoes, instead of sauce.Â  She watched on.Â  The pizza went in the oven, and she and I proceeded to find other activities.Â  When the pizza came out of the oven, I cut it, and grabbed a couple slices to photograph in better light.Â  As I turned around, I heard the scampering of little feet, and noticed the pie was shy a slice.Â  <a href="http://blommi.com/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza-recipe-and-a-giveaway/pizza-thief/" rel="attachment wp-att-22830"><img class="size-full wp-image-22830 aligncenter" title="pizza thief" src="http://blommi.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/pizza-thief.jpg" alt="pizza thief" width="300" height="224" /></a>It seems my wee pizza thief, was not about to wait for mom to plate this one.Â  She munched down on a couple slices in short time. I guess the potato pizza loving French was coming out in her&#8230;lol. I topped a couple leftover slices with deli turkey and melted cheese the next day for lunch.Â  It was quite yummy!</p><p style="text-align: left;">Here is the simple recipe, if you want to try this with your kids.</p><h3><a href="http://blommi.com/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza-recipe-and-a-giveaway/betty-crocker-au-gratin/" rel="attachment wp-att-22922"><img class="size-medium wp-image-22922 alignright" title="betty crocker au gratin potatoes" src="http://blommi.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/betty-crocker-au-gratin-275x300.jpg" alt="betty crocker au gratin potatoes" width="220" height="240" /></a>Au Gratin Potato and Bacon Pizza Recipe</h3><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Ingredients:</strong></span></p><p>bagged pizza dough</p><p>box of Betty Crocker Au Gratin potatoes (prepared according to stove top directions)</p><p>1/2 cup of shredded cheddar cheese</p><p>6-10 crispy slices of bacon</p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Directions:</strong></span></p><ol><li>Preheat oven to 450Â°</li><li>Stretch dough, on baking sheet which has been lightly oiled.</li><li>Evenly spread the Betty Crocket Au Gratin potatoes over the dough.</li><li>Top with the shredded cheddar and bacon.</li><li>Bake on middle rack for 22-26 minutes, until crust is nice and crisp.</li><li>Place on an old kitchen towel for cutting (keeps crust crispy).</li></ol><p><a href="http://blommi.com/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza-recipe-and-a-giveaway/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza/" rel="attachment wp-att-22829"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-22829" title="au gratin potato and bacon pizza" src="http://blommi.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/au-gratin-potato-and-bacon-pizza.jpg" alt="au gratin potato and bacon pizza" width="400" height="300" /></a></p><p>While I of course would love to have you try my recipe, there are many delicious and easy recipe ideas that incorporate Betty Crocker Specialty potatoes, at the <strong><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.bhg.com/recipes/quick-easy/dinners-tonight/');"  href="http://www.bhg.com/recipes/quick-easy/dinners-tonight/" target="_blank">Spud Hub</a></strong> on BHG.com.Â  I encourage you to stop in and browse the recipes there. You may just find that perfect dish for tonight&#8217;s supper.Â  Enter their sweepstakes while you are there too.Â  They are giving away some $250 gift cards.</p><p><em>Disclosure: I was given the opportunity to share my experience with Betty Crocker Specialty Potatoes, as part of a sponsored blogging program.Â  IÂ  was compensated for my participation. All opinions and recipes presented here are my own.</em></p><h3>Giveaway</h3><p>One lucky Blommi reader will win a <strong>$50 Visa Gift Card</strong>, so they can create a special meal for their own family, featuring Betty Crocker Specialty Potatoes</p><p><strong>Entry Options </strong>(do as many or as few as you like, but make sure to leave a separate comment for each entry)<strong><br /> </strong></p><ul><ul><ul><li>Visit the Spud Hub, and tell me your favorite recipe there.<br /> <strong> </strong></li><li>Follow this blog via email or RSSÂ  (One entry each).</li><li>Follow <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/twitter.com/twimommi');"  href="http://twitter.com/twimommi" target="_blank">@TwiMommi</a> on Twitter and tweet about this giveaway can be done 3x per day <strong>at least 1 hour apart</strong> (account must be public and have at least 50 followers). feel free to use this tweet: &#8221; <em>Win a $50 